Headlines.Headline: Google's Grand Bargain

PARAGRAPH.#text:
After two years of to-and-fro-ing, one of the world's most ubiquitous companies, Google Inc., has struck a deal with the European Union regulators to address concerns that it is abusing its dominance in search and online advertising.
The EU side is arguing that the proposals mark a huge leap forward and will rein in Google's ability to squeeze out rivals and would force the search engine giant to better label its products.
But there are plenty of critics who fear that the changes will, in the end, be mostly cosmetic and will do little to address concerns about how Google's overwhelming might in Europe, where it enjoys a market share of over 90%.
